  "text": "It is worth mentioning that underlying assumption in many CS-based studies is that the signal is sparse in nature or can be sparsely represented in a properly chosen basis. Indeed, applications of CS in wireless communications have been mainly on the recovery of naturally sparse signals such as sparse millimetre wave channel estimation in angle and delay domains, angle (DoA/AoD) estimation, and spectrum sensing [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Intriguing feature of SVT over these is to purposely transmit the sparse vector to achieve the gain in performance, latency, and energy efficiency.",
